BusinessTech is the largest and most influential business publication in South Africa, and the perfect platform for executive thought leadership. Read by millions of readers each month, the majority of BusinessTech’s audience consists of C-level executives, business owners, company directors, managers, and professionals. This includes: CEO/Director – 131,000
Business Owner – 856,000
Senior Management – 712,000 These readers are highly influential in the companies they work for, and are responsible for a range of strategic and purchasing decisions. This makes BusinessTech the ideal place for an executive to position themselves as a thought leader, and ensure they are reaching the right audience. BusinessTech offers excellent solutions that will elevate an executive as a thought leader in their industry. The first is a Thought Leadership Content package, which allows an executive to publish their thought leadership articles on BusinessTech. Alternatively, the content package can be used to publish executive Q&A articles on BusinessTech. This content is published on BusinessTech and posted to our Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn pages. The second option is an Executive Interview on Business Talk with Michael Avery. As South Africa’s leading online business talk show, this video interview provides excellent exposure to a business-focused audience – and is shared across all BusinessTech’s channels. To find out more, contact BusinessTech’s marketing team.